---

<Layout title={`Page ${page} - Project Prosthetic`}>
	<h1>Page {page}</h1>

	{pageNumber === 1 && (
		<>
			<h2>Introduction to Project Prosthetic</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				It was <b>October 2nd, 1998 in Kuwait City.</b>
				</p>
				<p>
				Fahad stands at the window of his classroom, his gaze drifting over the bustling streets of Kuwait City. The sun cast a warm glow over the buildings, a stark contrast to the memories that haunted him from his childhood. The scars of war were still evident, as the city was slowly healing, just as he was.
				</p>
				He vividly remembers a time before the chaos, before the scars. "Life felt peaceful and full of promise," he thinks as he looks down at his arm solemnly remembering the trauma he endured. At the time he was but a schoolboy, just days away from the start of 5th grade, eager to play another season for his school's badminton team. Being one of the strongest members of his team he had been confident in his abilities but the afternoon of August 2nd,1990, that would all change. 
				<p>
				</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 2 && (
		<>
			<h2>The Bombing.</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				“While having a joyful family gathering, the ground began to shake as we heard bombs and sirens overhead. Shortly after, the house came crashing down on us while we were eating" he recalled. It was a struggle to get out from under the bricks and rubble but the adrenaline in my body was so high that when we came out from the rubble, I hadn't even noticed that half my arm was missing until my mother ran up to me with concern and fear in her gaze. A shrapnel entered my arm during the bombing that night, leaving me permanently disabled. "In seconds, the life we knew was gone."
				</p>
				<p>
				The days that followed were a blur of fear and uncertainty. Our family was forced into a concentration camp. "We had no clean water, no clean clothes, no money," he remembered. We lived in a tent, while the war continued around us. There were no doctors, no support systems, and no access to prosthetics. As a child, I had to learn what it meant to live with a disability in the middle of a war zone.
				</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 3 && (
		<>
			<h2>Going to College...</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				Now, as a college student, I have found ways to adapt. I can no longer play badminton so I decided the only way I could succeed was by focusing on my studies and hobby of tinkering with technology. I was often singled out, but Ayla, my childhood friend who was always like a sister to me, was always by my side.
				</p>
				<p>
				As of right now I am majoring in biochemistry, still trying to make my dreams of becoming a Neurosurgeon into a reality. With my amputated arm, I felt for a long time that these dreams were delusions. After tedious amounts of  research, I discovered that there is still hope for people like me when I found out a successful Orthopedic Surgeon in Kuwait was an amputee, and she became my inspiration. 
				</p>
				<p>
				Meanwhile, Ayla majored in Industrial and Operations Engineering, a blend of Business and Engineering, as she has a passion for both. One day, in her class, the professor invites a Biomedical Engineer to speak with the class about disability aid, that's when an idea sparked in Aylas head. She decides to make Fahad a prosthetic arm after realizing how hard it is for him to live without one, and that it could really help him out now that he has a closer accessibility to having one.
				</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 4 && (
		<>
			<h2>As I was doing research:</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<ul>
					<li>The oldest prosthetic named the “Cairo toe” was dated back to 15 BC. This shows that even back then, people found ways to restore what was lost.</li>
					<li>The number of amputees was around 60 million, in 2017. (hasn’t been calculated since then)</li>
					<li>3 million people worldwide have arm amputations, and 2.4 million out of those are from disadvantaged countries.</li>
					<li>2 million out of 40 million surveyed amputees, have prosthetics.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="quiz-calculator-container">
				<div class="quiz-section">
					<Quiz questions={
						[
							{
								question: "Calculate the ratio of the amount of people who can get prosthetics, if the amount of amputees is ~~60,000,000 worldwide (USE THE DATA ABOVE):",
								options: ["25,000,000", "3,000,000", "3,333,334", "67,676,767"],
								correctAnswer: 1
							}
						]
					} shortAnswerQuestions={empty} />
				</div>
				<div class="calculator-section">
					<h2>Desmos Calculator</h2>
					<p>Use this embedded Desmos calculator for your mathematical needs!</p>
					<div class="calculator-container">
						<iframe src="https://www.desmos.com/calculator/scientific" width="100%" height="500" style="border: 1px solid #ccc" frameborder="0"></iframe>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 5 && (
		<>
			<h2>Ayla wants to build a prosthetic...</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
					Ayla, with the help from her professor, created a very rudimentary prosthetic using EMG (ElectroMyography, it amplifies electrical signals in the muscles, and lets it become interpretable for microcontrollers). It was her first prosthetic, and its capabilities extended to it picking up cups and mugs. Ayla worked hard as she created the prosthetic. Unfortunately, it took a lot of trial and error for Ayla to custom fit my stub, especially because Ayla had to model and 3D print it multiple times. Ayla then presented this prosthetic to me. She was unsure when she showed me the prosthetic, as it was her first time building one, and told me that there was a risk with trying it on.
				</p>
				<p>
				<b>
				CHOICE: Trust Ayla’s prosthetic? There is a small risk of nerve damage, if electricity flows back. She double checked the wires, multiple times, and got the ‘OK’ from the professor's friend…
				</b>
				</p>
				<p><a href={`/page/7`}>Trust it?</a></p>
				<p><a href={`/page/6`}>Don't try it?</a></p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 7 && (
		<>
			<h2>Trust it?</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				After further research, Ayla and I noticed that there are a lot of countries and people that struggle from the lack of aid devices being distributed to those areas. For example, we saw a statistic made from South Dakota State University, they stated that out of 40 million people only two million of them have prosthetics.  As someone who has personally gone through this, this touched me deeply. So, we both made it our mission to start a company and solve this issue.
				</p>
				<p style="color:#B9D9EB">
				<b>
				Me and Ayla founded Project Prosthetic  
				</p>
				</b>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 6 && (
		<>
			<h2>Not believing it...</h2>
			<p>
			Fahad continues his life but his dreams of becoming a surgeon aren't coming into reality or he doesn’t become as successful as he would have with the prosthetic Ayla has made for him. 
			</p>
		</>
	)}
	
	{pageNumber === 8 && (
		<>
			<h2>Bad start...</h2>
			<p>
			Fahad and Ayla really were determined about this company. Unfortunately the company did not have a good start and did not get a lot of traction from people. After multiple other tries on starting up the company it still failed. Fahad and Ayla became really unmotivated to pick the company back up.
			</p>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 9 && (
		<>
			<h2>More questions...</h2>
			<div class="content">
			</div>
			<div class="quiz-calculator-container">
				<div class="quiz-section">
					<Quiz questions={
						[
							{
								question: "If there are 60 million amputees in the world, and 24,000 are girls, what is the ratio of boys to girls that are amputees?",
								options: ["59,976,000:24,000", "3,000,000:24,000", "59,976,000:21,000"],
								correctAnswer: 0
							}
						]
					} shortAnswerQuestions={empty} />
				</div>
				<div class="calculator-section">
					<h2>Desmos Calculator</h2>
					<p>Use this embedded Desmos calculator for your mathematical needs!</p>
					<div class="calculator-container">
						<iframe src="https://www.desmos.com/calculator/scientific" width="100%" height="500" style="border: 1px solid #ccc" frameborder="0"></iframe>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 10 && (
		<>
			<h2>Try again?</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				<b>
				CHOICE: After several setbacks, it seems like it's not going to work out. Should I walk away from the company, or give it another shot?
				</b>
				</p>
				<p><a href={`/page/12`}>Push forward</a></p>
				<p><a href={`/page/11`}>Give up.</a></p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 11 && (
		<>
			<h2>You gave up.</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				I accepted that it wasn't going to work out. I walked away from the company, but I wasn’t ready to give up entirely. So, I ended up as a surgical assistant. It wasn’t my dream of neurosurgery, but being in that room, helping with life-changing procedures, felt like I was finally where I was meant to be.
				</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 12 && (
		<>
			<h2>You reluctantly push forward.</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				After facing setbacks and failures, we weren’t really going to give up. We knew our vision was worth pursuing, so we decided to try again, but with a fresh approach. 
				</p>
				<p>
				This time, we took a hard look at our mistakes, refined our business model, and focused on learning from the past. We were determined to make it work. Failure wasn’t an option anymore—it was a lesson we were ready to learn and grow from.
				</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 13 && (
		<>
			<h2>More questions...</h2>
			<div class="quiz-calculator-container">
				<div class="quiz-section">
					<Quiz questions={
						[
							{
								question: "If 3 million people worldwide have arm amputations, and 2.4 million out of those are from disadvantaged countries, calculate the ratio of people with amputations globally, and people from disadvantaged countries, with an arm amputation.",
								options: ["60m:2.4m", "67m:4.2m", "2.4m:2.4m"],
								correctAnswer: 0
							}
						]
					} shortAnswerQuestions={empty} />
				</div>
				<div class="calculator-section">
					<h2>Desmos Calculator</h2>
					<p>Use this embedded Desmos calculator for your mathematical needs!</p>
					<div class="calculator-container">
						<iframe src="https://www.desmos.com/calculator/scientific" width="100%" height="500" style="border: 1px solid #ccc" frameborder="0"></iframe>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 14 && (
		<>
			<h2>Ayla's 3D printing journey!</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				A few months later, Ayla tried to create a mold with 3D printing, in hopes of improving the older prosthetic Ayla’s Silicone Stub Socket™, surprisingly fit perfectly on my stub. This freed up a lot of time for me and Ayla, as she no longer had to custom fit the prosthetics to my stub, but now to the socket, and I could easily attach and remove prosthetics quickly. These prosthetics could also be swapped between users, as now it is only a magnetic fit, and the EMG technology was fit into the stub itself. Since it takes a long time to make the sockets fit the people so they can use the prosthetics, using molds makes it a lot easier.
				</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 15 && (
		<>
			<h2>Help Ayla Code!</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				Ayla's new prosthetic requires more advanced code. Edit the code if Fahad's prosthetic EMG sensor, outputs 700 at highest muscle flexion.

				<CodeEditor 
					title="Fix the Prosthetic Code"
					description="Change the actuation point from 300 to 700"
					initialCode={`
#include <Servo.h>
Servo pointer, middle, ring, pinky, thumb;




int muscleInputAnalog = 3;
int val = 0;
  void setup()
  {
    pointer.attach(5);
    middle.attach(6);
    ring.attach(7);
    pinky.attach(8);
    thumb.attach(9);
    Serial.begin(9600);
  }
  void loop()
{
  val = analogRead(muscleInputAnalog);
  Serial.println(val);
  if( val > 300)
  {
    thumb.write(180);
    pointer.write(180);
    middle.write(180);
    ring.write(180);
    pinky.write(180);
   
  }
else{
    thumb.write(0);
    pointer.write(0);
    middle.write(0);
    ring.write(0);
    pinky.write(0);
    delay(100);
  }
  }

					`}
					expectedCode={`
#include <Servo.h>
Servo pointer, middle, ring, pinky, thumb;




int muscleInputAnalog = 3;
int val = 0;
  void setup()
  {
    pointer.attach(5);
    middle.attach(6);
    ring.attach(7);
    pinky.attach(8);
    thumb.attach(9);
    Serial.begin(9600);
  }
  void loop()
{
  val = analogRead(muscleInputAnalog);
  Serial.println(val);
  if( val > 700)
  {
    thumb.write(180);
    pointer.write(180);
    middle.write(180);
    ring.write(180);
    pinky.write(180);
   
  }
else{
    thumb.write(0);
    pointer.write(0);
    middle.write(0);
    ring.write(0);
    pinky.write(0);
    delay(100);
  }
  }

					`}
					hint="Look for the value gate, and change it from 300 to 700"
				/>

				
				</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

	{pageNumber === 16 && (
		<>
			<h2>The second prosthetic...</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				Ayla then made the second version prosthetic, made out of carbon fiber enthralled in kevlar, and then infused with a gold-titanium alloy, as this material proved to be the most strong, after extensive testing. This prosthetic is fire resistant and can function in extreme temperatures. 
				</p>
				<p>
				Because of this one of a kind design, it got a lot of traction in the market.
				</p>
				<p>
				Over time, they continue to build and develop more prosthetics. Their designs were very unique and they became very famous for their new and developed prosthetics. Their goal for the company was to distribute prosthetics to people all around the world, specifically people who are amputees in war torn nations. 
				</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}
	{pageNumber === 17 && (
		<>
			<h2>Conclusion</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>
				One day, Fahad and Ayla were in the elevator as they were leaving for a meeting. There, they met a boy named Mateo, with a prosthetic leg, who looked about 10-11 years old. He looked at Fahad and Ayla, with hope in his eyes, as he said; “Thank you so much! I can finally play soccer again!” This interaction helped them both realize how many lives they have touched with the work they did.
				</p>
				<p>
				We knew we were creating more than just functional products; we were providing a lifeline, a new beginning for many who had lost so much.
				</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}


	<div class="navigation">
		{pageNumber === 1 && <a href={`/index.html`} class="nav-button prev">Home</a>}
		{pageNumber > 1 && pageNumber != 6 && pageNumber != 12 && pageNumber != 7 && pageNumber != 11 &&<a href={`/page/${pageNumber - 1}`} class="nav-button prev">Previous Page</a>}
